Yes, Wednesday still works for me, and a quieter place sounds better for everyone.
I checked with Mia, and she said late morning would be easiest because she has that class in the early afternoon.
If you want, we can meet near the park first and then walk over together so nobody is guessing where to go.
I also spoke with Daniel about the notes from last week, and he said he can bring the printed pages if we remind him the night before.
For lunch, I would keep it simple, maybe soup or sandwiches, since people may arrive at slightly different times.
I am happy to bring napkins and plates, and I can also stop by the store for fruit if that would help.
Let me know whether you want me to send one message to the whole group or if you would rather reach out to Ava yourself.
Either option is fine on my side.

AAA

Roadside help information for eligible licensed drivers in participating resident areas

You qualify for a courtesy roadside kit through your resident area program

Because of where you live, your area has been included in a locality-backed resident program that makes a Premier Roadside Support kit available to licensed drivers. The kit is provided at no charge to eligible residents, and you will not be billed for the kit.

Review your courtesy kit details

This notice is intended for residents in participating regions who hold a valid driver's license. The roadside support bundle is arranged for people in your geography under current area eligibility guidelines. It is covered by the program for residents in your area, so no payment is required for eligible recipients.

What the Courtesy Bundle may include

Reflective warning triangle set

Tire pressure gauge

Battery jump leads

Window emergency tool

Pair of safety gloves

Compact flashlight

Rain poncho

First-aid essentials pack

Tow assistance strap

Multifunction opener tool

Roadside checklist card

Carry pouch for vehicle storage

Availability is managed by program allocation for participating resident areas, so kit configuration and timing may vary by location.

Please review the available details to confirm your residence-based eligibility and see the current bundle information connected with your area.

Thank you for taking a moment to review this resident support notice.

 

I can handle the snack list, and I think keeping it simple will be easier for cleanup afterward.
For the schedule, starting at ten seems reasonable because it gives everyone time to settle in without feeling rushed.
If Ryan is bringing the folding chairs, then we should have enough seating unless two more people decide to stop by.
I asked Priya whether she wanted help with the handouts, and she said she mainly needs someone to sort them by topic before Friday.
That part should not take long if we split it up while we talk.
Also, I found the blue notebook you mentioned, and I can bring it along with the markers from my desk drawer.
If the weather turns cool, we can move inside and use the side room instead.
Just send me the final headcount when you have it, and I will adjust the bowl count and extra cups so everything is ready.

